Top 6 Baby Names in WY years 1912-2020

Micky Steinberg

9/20/2021

The Name Data

We start with the dataframe WY.csv from SSA.gov, which contains information about the number of children born with a given name, grouped by year and sex. The popularity_index refers to the percent of children (of the given sex) born that year with a given name. Note that the popularity index is computed as the proportion of total number of babies reported by the SSA for a given year, which is slightly smaller than the true number of babies, as the SSA only includes names given to at least 5 babies in a given year. The true number of babies born is approximately .5% or 1.5% greater (for males and females, respectively), and doesnt fluctuate drastically from year to year.

Now we will define a True Popularity Index of a name in a given year. This will be the approximate popularity of a name within its generation - that is, the prevalence of the name within a window of 5 years. I.e. for the year 1912, the popularity index is the (approximate) percent of children (of the given sex) born from 1910 to 1914 with the given name, and the ranking is determined by the number of children (of the given sex) born in that time frame with the given name.
